  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"y equals two sevenths x plus 3\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>y</mi>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mfrac>\n\t\t<mn>2</mn>\n\t\t<mn>7</mn>\n\t</mfrac>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t<mn>3</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">One of the two equations in a system of linear equations is given. The system has infinitely many solutions. If the second equation in the system is <math alttext=\"y equals m x plus b\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>y</mi>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mi>m</mi>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t\t<mi>b</mi>\n\t</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</math>, where <math alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math> are constants, what is the value of <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
